This recipe is a healthier alternative to your party treats and pastries.
These tasty filo parcels contain a herb and ricotta filling and have less
kilojoules and fat than many other fried appetizers or snacks.
Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Email Print
1. Place bok choy, onion, garlic, soy sauce, basil and ricotta cheese in a bowl. Mix until well combined
2. Lay one sheet filo pastry on the bench and fold lengthways into thirds
3. Spoon some of the mixture onto the top of the pastry strip. Fold pastry over to form a triangle and continue folding the pastry strip
4. Place triangle on a lightly greased tray. Continue to create filo triangles with the ricotta mixture, using a new sheet of filo each time
5. Lightly spray triangles with canola oil before baking in a moderate oven, 180C, for 10 minutes, or until golden brown
Filo pastry is much lighter and contains less fat than average pastries. Using
filo pastry instead of normal pastry can help to decrease kilojoules, total
fat and saturated fat. Don't forget your portion size is still very important
Recipe and image kindly provided by Sanitarium Health & Wellbeing Company.
Steer away from unhealthy comfort food and enjoy this delicious mix of roast
vegetables, pecan nuts and pasta with a hint of garlic and basil. A fantastic
A quick and easy satisfying meal for one - rich in healthy fats, carbohydrates
and fibre, not to mention a good source of calcium.
